title: The recent spread of coyotes across North America did not doom deer populations

title_detail.value: The recent spread of coyotes across North America did not doom deer populations

summary: Coyotes eat deer, but not enough to limit the deer population at a large scale. A new study of deer numbers across the eastern United States has found that the arrival and establishment of coyote predators has not caused the number of deer harvested by hunters to decline.
